# Trading safety (non-negotiable)

Every order, paper or live, passes through M7 `RiskGate.check()` before leaving M6. There is no path
around M7. Guardrails are enforced in code, not just in config UI.

## Mandatory pre-trade checks (reject + log on violation; never silently clamp)
1. Per-position stop-loss — no position opens without one.
2. Max position size (per symbol) and max gross exposure (portfolio) — hard caps.
3. Daily-drawdown kill-switch — cross the threshold → flatten all positions and HALT until manual reset.

## Hard rules
- No LLM call anywhere in M6 or M7. Execution and risk are deterministic and fully tested.
- Live start requires a passing ValidationReport AND an Approval row tied to the exact strategy_version
  and a user_id. Assert both before the runtime starts.
- PDT guard: intraday mode + account equity < $25,000 → block live intraday with a clear error; offer swing mode.
- The assistant may execute read and risk_reducing (pause/flatten/halt) actions; risk_increasing actions
  (deploy-live/approve/raise-limit/place-order) are staged for human confirm only — never auto-executed.
- Every signal, order, fill, rejection, kill-switch event, and approval is written to the immutable audit log.
- Tests MUST include drills proving stop-loss, position cap, gross-exposure cap, and the daily kill-switch fire.
- Fail closed: when unsure whether an action is safe, reject and log — never fail open.
